hey anon. i use the rigify plugin for all my character models.
this is for blender v2.9, but everything about the workflow is generally the same in blender v4, it shows how to parent models to the rig: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DS885Sk1gSs
here's how you'd add a tail to your rigify base, make sure do do this before generating your rig: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vYo3JNx3lTo
this guy makes a bunch of very quick and fantastic blender tips and tutorials. his weight painting videos are a good watch if your mesh/character model isn't moving correctly with the rig: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PLWv9yjVaoU
you can find the rig's weight bones by making the "DEF" layer visible, webm related.
last but not least, there are a handful of MSC game models on my gitlab, they are rigged with rigify and have went through multiple versions of blender since the debut of the game itself. you can study them for yourself here: https://gitlab.com/spacedimsum
have fun, dude!!
